<item>
            <title>[SPARK-23486] LookupFunctions should not check the same function name more than once</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SPARK-23486</link>
                <project id="12315420" key="SPARK">Spark</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;For a query invoking the same function multiple times, the current&#160;&lt;tt&gt;LookupFunctions&lt;/tt&gt; rule performs a check for each invocation. For users using Hive metastore as external catalog, this issues unnecessary metastore accesses and can slow down the analysis phase quite a bit.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="13140082">SPARK-23486</key>
            <summary>LookupFunctions should not check the same function name more than once</summary>
