                            <comment id="16372285" author="lian cheng" created="Thu, 22 Feb 2018 01:15:16 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Please refer to &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SPARK-19737?focusedCommentId=16371377&amp;amp;page=com.atlassian.jira.plugin.system.issuetabpanels:comment-tabpanel#comment-16371377&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;this comment&lt;/a&gt; for more details.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="16373851" author="kevinyu98" created="Fri, 23 Feb 2018 03:05:09 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Hello &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=lian+cheng&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;lian cheng&quot;&gt;lian cheng&lt;/a&gt;: I think the easy way is to build a hash map&#160;around the LookupFunctions, if the function exists in the external catalog,&#160; put into the hash map for the first time, next time when call the LookupFunctions, first check the hash map to avoid the metastore accesses, does this approach look ok to you? If you think it is ok, I can provide a pr for reviewing. Thanks.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Another approach is to&#160;cache the external catalog functions in the share state,&#160; many queries can use, but it will be more involved to do the invalidation.&#160;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
